title: For Sale:  Sheridan Blue Streak Air Rifle .20 cal/ 5mm
postcontent:
Sheridan Blue Streak Air Rifle 20 cal/ 5mm

The Sheridan Blue Streak 5mm is still considered one of the best, rugged, hard hitting pellet guns around and has a loyal following. I acquired this pellet gun circa 1976 when in college and used it to cleanly bag a considerable number of rabbits, squirrels, and even game birds, some on the fly for my meals as a poor college student. It has only been used a few times since college to train newbies to shooting. It is still in excellent condition. It is very point and shoot and very accurate; you can shoot groups that a quarter can cover at 20 yards; the trigger is very light. All the seals are original and still in great shape.

The blue on the gun is 90-95 percent with no scratches. The top tube has very slight glueing wear where the tub hood slide over it. The stock has some dings in it consistent with its age, but the finish still looks great; I tried to capture that in the photos. There is some where under the lever handle where the lever contacts the air chamber. While I hadn't shot it in a coue decades or more,  the gun has been kept lubricated. It has never been disassembled. The mechanics appear to be perfect and I attribute that to how robust the gun is made.

The scope is missing the caps to elevation/windage adjustments, but otherwise is in good shape. The mounts are made for the gun, they were called B- Square mounts if memory serves.

I shot it several times before listing it and it is still accurate, hitting dead on at 35yrd with Beeman Silver Jets and it Zipped through both sides of a heavy gage soup can with 10 pumps, barely moving the can. When I used to use it for small game, I used to use between 10-15 pumps. I tested it with 15 with no issues.

Additional photos can be requested.

postcontent:
Well, I've decided to see if I can sell this beauty that hardly ever shoot. It took me a while to finally get one of these but my mind has moved on to something else. I picked this rifle up from a very reputable collector/restoration hobbyist so I can tell you that beyond any doubt, this rifle is period correct down to the springs. The seller broke this rifle down part by part to show me each proof mark to prove to me that she's all correct by the book so after seeing me the parts and book laid out in front of me, I can say this beauty is a piece of art. 

The cool part about this rifle is that it has an original 1909 barrel on it that is correct for the receiver and this rifle is a former USMC rifle. The reason I can tell you that is that the receiver has the "Hatcher Hole" which was a USMC trademark. 

Anyways, I'm looking to get $1500 OBRO for this fine collectors piece.  I may take offers of trades, but cash is king.

title: For Sale:  Thompson M1 (A1 overstamp) SMG parts kit
postcontent:
Here is the Holy Grail of all firearms & history buff pieces. This is an early WWII production Thompson M1 (A1 overstamp, rare) SMG Kit. 90% matching/complete.

This is a rare find and quite the conversation piece. Only to increase in value.

-*Disclaimer*-This is a demilled parts kit and is not functional as it is. This kit is fully legal to own and build as a non functional display piece. All NFA rules/Laws are to be followed.

The receiver sections that are there are extremely rare due to their size. Most commonly these are cut into 1" sections. There is however a 1.5" piece missing from the middle. Typical of bring back guns being demilled when the 1987 ban went into effect.  Have seen sections such as these 2 pieces sell for $1000 by themselves.

The bolt is a rare type that I can only find described as the "lightning bolt". Basically it's has slots milled out of it to reduce surface area and drag and also make the bolt itself lighter increasing the cyclic rate. It is in extremely good condition. 

The lower shows little abuse but honest wear. The stock is missing the hardware other than the sling swivel. Complete lowers with internals minus stocks sell for over $500.

There are 2 spare bolts, these can be used as paper weights or I can keep them and reduce the asking price. They are also collectable and will increase in value.

There is also several extra receiver pieces. *These are not to be used to assemble this kit into a functional state. The missing section from the kit can be taken from the receiver section that has been bead blasted. This piece is not to be welded into place but can freely fill in the gap. *The receiver must remain cut into 3 pieces.  If you do not wish to have these I would reduce asking price and keep them.

Though missing some small pieces this kit is very collectable and valuble. It will only increase in value. I'm sad to put it up for sale but I have other things I need to take care of and want it to go to a good home.

$3400 Or Best Offer.

More pictures upon request.

Please ask any questions. 
Cross posted.
Reserve right to exit sale if I believe anything unscrupulous/illegal to come of its sale to the buyer.
Might consider the right trade.
